Turkey Equity Movers: Afyon, Akenerji, Global Menkul Are Active

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n   a n d   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-06-29T14:53:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/turkey-equity-movers-afyon-akenerji-global-menkul-are-active.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 183.80, or 0.3 percent, to 63,002.88 at the 5:30 p.m.
close in Istanbul, the highest since June 13.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Afyon Cimento Sanayi TAS (AFYON)  , a Turkish cement
maker, surged 13 liras, or 11 percent, to 132 liras, the biggest
increase since May 24. Italcementi SpA’s Ciments Français unit
hired Mediobanca SpA “to evaluate and implement strategic
alternatives” for the possible sale of its entire stake in
Afyon Cimento, according to a statement through the Italian
exchange yesterday.  Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR)   declined 9 kurus, or
2.4 percent, to 3.74 liras, the biggest drop since June 9. The
outcome of a process to sell assets of the Turkish utility,
owned by the  Czech Republic ’s CEZ AS and Turkey’s Akkok Group,
may “become clear” in the fall, Ahmet Umit Danisman, Akenerji
chief executive, told reporters in Istanbul today.  Global Menkul Degerler AS (GLBMDY TI), Global Yatirim
Holding AS’s broker unit known as Global Securities surged on
the first day of trading in Istanbul, rising 10 kurus, or 6.1
percent, to 1.75 liras. The broker sold 10 million shares, or a
25 percent stake, for 16.5 million liras ($10 million) in an
initial public offering on June 22, after getting 41 million
liras of demand, Hurriyet reported on June 23. Azimut Holding
SpA of  Italy  bought a 5 percent stake in Global Securities,
Global Yatirim said in a statement to the bourse after the close
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
